<REFENTRY id="awk">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>
awk
</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>awk</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
pattern scanning and processing language
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>
<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
<COMMAND>awk</COMMAND> is as specified in the Single UNIX
Specification but with differences as listed below.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

<refsect1>
<title>Differences</title>
<para>
Certain aspects of internationalized regular expressions are optional;
see <xref linkend="localization-regex" />.
</para>
</refsect1>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>LSB Deprecated Differences</TITLE>
<para>
<COMMAND>gawk</COMMAND> and <COMMAND>mawk</COMMAND> shall be Single
UNIX Specification compliant
implementations of the <COMMAND>awk</COMMAND> language.
However, <COMMAND>gawk</COMMAND> and <COMMAND>mawk</COMMAND> are
expected to disappear from a future version of the LSB; LSB
applications should invoke <COMMAND>awk</COMMAND> instead.
</para>
</REFSECT1>
</REFENTRY>
